<item>
            <title>[SPR-9722] Default values in property placeholder hierarchy applied too early</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-9722</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-4785&quot; title=&quot;Add support for default values in property placeholder syntax&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-4785&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-4785&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; support for default values was added.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, I observed that they are applied too early if you have a hierarchy or cascade of property placeholder configurers:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Spring loops through the prioritized list of configurers&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;if property X is not found in the first configurer the default value is returned&lt;br/&gt;
--&amp;gt; the whole list should be processed first before the default value is used&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
            <key id="45056">SPR-9722</key>
            <summary>Default values in property placeholder hierarchy applied too early</summary>
